4. Attention Mechanism
Definition

The Attention Mechanism allows the model to determine which previous words or tokens are most important when predicting the next token. It helps the model maintain context and understand relationships in the input.

Real-world Analogy

While reading a book, your brain naturally remembers the important characters and events instead of treating every sentence with equal importance.

Salesforce Example

Prompt:

"Sonal created an Apex Trigger. She deployed it successfully."

The model understands that "She" refers to "Sonal" using the attention mechanism.

